<quantity id="4CEF9B7FFFEFFFD1E62755DF8DCC9CD4" box="[1340,1428,942,969]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="7" pageNumber="206" unit="mm" value="2.5">2.5 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA8369AFFEFFFD1E3DC55A28AC89A2C" blockId="7.[151,1437,726,1689]" pageId="7" pageNumber="206">
<emphasis id="B963EA88FFEFFFD1E3DC55A2895F9CF0" bold="true" box="[199,263,979,1005]" pageId="7" pageNumber="206">Head</emphasis>
. In dorsal view, transverse,1.15–1.2× as wide as long (
<figureCitation id="132C2A1FFFEFFFD1E07555A28B989CF0" box="[878,960,978,1005]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–23. 9–11" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1899,1923]" captionTargetBox="[212,1376,181,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-27@8.[212,1376,181,1875]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 9–23. 9–11. Coelinius canastra Souza-Gessner &amp; Penteado-Dias; 12–14. Coelinius itamonte Souza-Gessner &amp; Penteado-Dias; 15–17. Coelinius kali Souza-Gessner &amp; Penteado-Dias; 18–20. Coelinius longicephalus sp. nov.; 21–23. Coelinius lux Souza-Gessner &amp; Penteado-Dias; 9, 12, 15, 18, 21 head, dorsal view, scale bar = 0.5 mm; 10, 13, 16, 19, 22 head, lateral view, scale bar = 0.5 mm; 11, 14, 17, 20, 23 mandible, lateral view, scale bar = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500719" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500719/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="206">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
), 1.1× as wide as eye, 1.2–1.3× as wide as mesosoma, 1.0–1.1× as wide as long (length of head in lateral view). Shortest distance from occiput to stemmaticum 0.7× stemmaticum height. Shortest distance from between outer margin of lateral ocellus and margin of eye 1.5– 1.6× stemmaticum width. In lateral view, head 1.1–1.2× as long as high (
<figureCitation id="132C2A1FFFEFFFD1E0D5524E8C7A9B47" box="[974,1058,1087,1114]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–23. 9–11" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1899,1923]" captionTargetBox="[212,1376,181,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-27@8.[212,1376,181,1875]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 9–23. 9–11. Coelinius canastra Souza-Gessner &amp; Penteado-Dias; 12–14. Coelinius itamonte Souza-Gessner &amp; Penteado-Dias; 15–17. Coelinius kali Souza-Gessner &amp; Penteado-Dias; 18–20. Coelinius longicephalus sp. nov.; 21–23. Coelinius lux Souza-Gessner &amp; Penteado-Dias; 9, 12, 15, 18, 21 head, dorsal view, scale bar = 0.5 mm; 10, 13, 16, 19, 22 head, lateral view, scale bar = 0.5 mm; 11, 14, 17, 20, 23 mandible, lateral view, scale bar = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500719" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500719/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="206">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
); temple 1.4–1.6× as long as eye. Eye 0.7–0.9× as long as high. Mandible 1.2–1.4× as long as apical width (
<figureCitation id="132C2A1FFFEFFFD1E0C252128C759B60" box="[985,1069,1123,1149]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–23. 9–11" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1899,1923]" captionTargetBox="[212,1376,181,1875]" captionTargetId="figure-27@8.[212,1376,181,1875]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 9–23. 9–11. Coelinius canastra Souza-Gessner &amp; Penteado-Dias; 12–14. Coelinius itamonte Souza-Gessner &amp; Penteado-Dias; 15–17. Coelinius kali Souza-Gessner &amp; Penteado-Dias; 18–20. Coelinius longicephalus sp. nov.; 21–23. Coelinius lux Souza-Gessner &amp; Penteado-Dias; 9, 12, 15, 18, 21 head, dorsal view, scale bar = 0.5 mm; 10, 13, 16, 19, 22 head, lateral view, scale bar = 0.5 mm; 11, 14, 17, 20, 23 mandible, lateral view, scale bar = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500719" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500719/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="206">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
). Face 1.6–2.0× as wide as high, 1.3–1.8× as wide as clypeus, 1.8–2.2× as high as clypeus. Clypeus 2.1–2.8× as wide as high. Paraclypeal fovea minute, occupying 0.5–0.6× of the distance from lateral margin of clypeus to eye. Maxillary palp 0.5× as long as head; third segment 0.8–0.9× as long as fourth. First flagellomere 2.65–3.1× as long as wide, 1.1–1.3× as long as second flagellomere. Second flagellomere 2.2–2.6× as long as wide. Third flagellomere 1.9–2.15× as long as wide. Tenth flagellomere 1.5–1.7× as long as wide.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA8369AFFEFFFD1E3DC534A8C8E9A48" blockId="7.[151,1437,726,1689]" box="[199,1238,1338,1366]" pageId="7" pageNumber="206">
<emphasis id="B963EA88FFEFFFD1E3DC534A891D9A48" bold="true" box="[199,325,1339,1365]" pageId="7" pageNumber="206">Mesosoma</emphasis>
. 1.85–2.1× as long as head (lateral view). Mesoscutum 1.0–1.1× as wide as long.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA8369AFFEFFFD1E3DC532E8C809A80" blockId="7.[151,1437,726,1689]" pageId="7" pageNumber="206">
<emphasis id="B963EA88FFEFFFD1E3DC532E88A79A64" bold="true" box="[199,255,1375,1401]" pageId="7" pageNumber="206">Legs</emphasis>
. Hind femur 4.5–4.9× as long as wide. Hind tibia 10.4–10.9× as long as its maximum subapical width, 1.1–1.2× as long as hind tarsus. First segment of hind tarsus 1.6–1.8× as long as second segment.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA8369AFFEFFFD1E3DC53D68A849914" blockId="7.[151,1437,726,1689]" pageId="7" pageNumber="206">
<emphasis id="B963EA88FFEFFFD1E3DC53D689189ADD" bold="true" box="[199,320,1446,1473]" pageId="7" pageNumber="206">Fore wing</emphasis>
. 0.8–0.85× as long as body. Vein 1-SR+M 0.9–1.05× as long as 2-SR; 2-SR+M 0.2–0.3× as long as 2-SR. First subdiscal cell closed, CU1a arising distinctly below middle of subdiscal cell; cu-a postfurcal, 0.9–1.0× as long as 1-CU1; 2-CU1 0.9–1.0× as long as m-cu.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA8369AFFEFFFD1E3DC50638C19994C" blockId="7.[151,1437,726,1689]" pageId="7" pageNumber="206">
<emphasis id="B963EA88FFEFFFD1E3DC5063891E9931" bold="true" box="[199,326,1554,1580]" pageId="7" pageNumber="206">Hind wing</emphasis>
. With three hamuli, 4.9–5.3× as long as wide. Vein 1-M 0.4–0.5× as long as M+CU, 1.1–1.6× as long as 1r-m. Subbasal cell closed. Vein m-cu absent; SR and 2-M spectral through.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA8369AFFEFFFD1E3DC502A892C9984" blockId="7.[151,1437,726,1689]" pageId="7" pageNumber="206">
<emphasis id="B963EA88FFEFFFD1E3DC502A891B9968" bold="true" box="[199,323,1627,1653]" pageId="7" pageNumber="206">Metasoma</emphasis>
. 1.1× as long as head plus mesosoma length. First metasomal tergite with apex 1.1–1.2× as wide as base; dorsope deep.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
